Scores of Nompumelelo residents were displaced yesterday when about 25 shacks burnt down. There were no reported injuries.Some helpless residents had to watch as their homes burnt down while others tried to salvage the little they could.It was not yet clear how many shacks had burnt and what caused the fire.For the full story get a copy of the Dispatch or subscribe to our e-Edition for the complete newspaper with jobs, classifieds, crosswords, TV schedules and back editions.